\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces IMDB: ROC-AUC curves for all 8 models. Transformer (AUC=0.968) and SVM (AUC=0.961) perform best. Decision Tree (AUC=0.776) and KNN (AUC=0.793) are the weakest.}}{6}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:imdb_roc}{{4}{6}{}{}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces IMDB: F1-Macro vs.\ F1-Weighted comparison across all 8 models. The two bars are nearly identical for every model, which confirms that IMDB is a perfectly balanced binary dataset (50\% positive / 50\% negative). On balanced datasets, macro and weighted averaging give the same result, so accuracy alone is a reliable metric here. The ranking is consistent with Table~\ref {tab:imdb_results}: Transformer $>$ SVM $\approx $ Logistic Regression $>$ Naive Bayes $\approx $ Random Forest $\approx $ XGBoost $>$ Decision Tree $\approx $ KNN.}}{6}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:imdb_f1}{{5}{6}{}{}{}}
